body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello, thank you for contacting Ross Motors customer support. My name is Jordan Ross. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hello Jordan, my name is Lauren Brooks.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great to meet you, Lauren. To assist you better, may I please have your date of birth?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, it's the twenty third of December, nineteen eighty five.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Lauren. Can you also provide me with the last four digits of your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course, it's eight three zero six.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you for providing that information, Lauren. Is there anything else I can assist you with today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: No, that's all. Thank you for your help, Jordan.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: You're welcome, Lauren. Thank you for reaching out. Have a great day!
